 {"id":"beads_rust-1rpr","title":"Implement ProgressTracker component","description":"## Component: ProgressTracker

### Purpose
Shows real-time progress for long-running operations like `sync`, `lint` (many issues), and bulk operations. Provides visual feedback WITHOUT blocking agent JSON output.

### File Location
`src/format/components/progress.rs`

### CRITICAL: Mode Behavior
Progress output MUST be to **stderr** so it doesn't corrupt stdout JSON:
- Rich/Plain: Progress bar to stderr
- JSON: NO progress output (agents parse stdout)
- Quiet: NO progress output

### CRITICAL: Integration with Existing Code
Must check OutputContext mode before showing progress:
```rust
if ctx.is_json() || ctx.is_quiet() {
    return ProgressHandle::noop();  // Silent handle
}
```

### API Design
```rust
use crate::format::OutputContext;

pub struct ProgressTracker<'a> {
    ctx: &'a OutputContext,
    total: Option<u64>,
    message: String,
    style: ProgressStyle,
}

pub enum ProgressStyle {
    Bar,      // [████████░░░░] 67% 
    Spinner,  // ⠋ Processing...
    Counter,  // Processed 42/100 issues
}

impl<'a> ProgressTracker<'a> {
    pub fn new(ctx: &'a OutputContext) -> Self;
    pub fn with_total(mut self, total: u64) -> Self;
    pub fn with_message(mut self, msg: &str) -> Self;
    pub fn style(mut self, style: ProgressStyle) -> Self;
    pub fn start(&mut self) -> ProgressHandle;
}

pub struct ProgressHandle {
    inner: Option<indicatif::ProgressBar>,  // None for JSON/quiet mode
}

impl ProgressHandle {
    pub fn noop() -> Self { Self { inner: None } }
    pub fn inc(&self, delta: u64);
    pub fn set_message(&self, msg: &str);
    pub fn finish(&self);
}
```

### Mode Behavior
- Rich: Animated progress bar with percentage
- Plain: Simple text updates (no ANSI)
- JSON: Silent (no output)
- Quiet: Silent (no output)

---

## Testing Requirements

### Unit Tests
Location: tests/format/progress_tests.rs

```rust
use beads_rust::format::components::{ProgressTracker, ProgressStyle, ProgressHandle};
use beads_rust::format::OutputContext;

#[test]
fn test_progress_bar_style() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::plain();
    let mut tracker = ProgressTracker::new(&ctx)
        .with_total(100)
        .style(ProgressStyle::Bar);
    let handle = tracker.start();
    handle.inc(50);
    // In plain mode, should show progress
    handle.finish();
}

#[test]
fn test_progress_spinner_style() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::plain();
    let mut tracker = ProgressTracker::new(&ctx)
        .with_message("Processing...")
        .style(ProgressStyle::Spinner);
    let handle = tracker.start();
    // Spinner should work without total
    handle.set_message("Still processing...");
    handle.finish();
}

#[test]
fn test_progress_json_mode_silent() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::json();
    let mut tracker = ProgressTracker::new(&ctx)
        .with_total(100)
        .style(ProgressStyle::Bar);
    let handle = tracker.start();
    // Handle should be noop
    assert!(handle.is_noop());
    handle.inc(50);  // Should not crash
    handle.finish();  // Should not crash
}

#[test]
fn test_progress_quiet_mode_silent() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::quiet();
    let mut tracker = ProgressTracker::new(&ctx)
        .with_total(100);
    let handle = tracker.start();
    assert!(handle.is_noop());
}

#[test]
fn test_progress_handle_noop() {
    let handle = ProgressHandle::noop();
    assert!(handle.is_noop());
    // All operations should be no-ops
    handle.inc(100);
    handle.set_message("ignored");
    handle.finish();
}

#[test]
fn test_progress_counter_style() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::plain();
    let mut tracker = ProgressTracker::new(&ctx)
        .with_total(100)
        .style(ProgressStyle::Counter);
    let handle = tracker.start();
    handle.inc(42);
    // Should show "42/100"
    handle.finish();
}

#[test]
fn test_progress_with_message() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::plain();
    let mut tracker = ProgressTracker::new(&ctx)
        .with_total(100)
        .with_message("Syncing");
    let handle = tracker.start();
    assert!(handle.message().contains("Syncing") || true);  // If message is accessible
}

#[test]
fn test_progress_outputs_to_stderr() {
    // Progress should NOT corrupt stdout
    // This is critical for JSON mode compatibility
    let ctx = OutputContext::plain();
    let mut tracker = ProgressTracker::new(&ctx).with_total(10);

    // Capture stdout and stderr
    let handle = tracker.start();
    handle.inc(5);
    handle.finish();

    // Stdout should be empty (all progress to stderr)
}

#[test]
fn test_progress_finish_clears() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::plain();
    let mut tracker = ProgressTracker::new(&ctx).with_total(100);
    let handle = tracker.start();
    handle.inc(100);
    handle.finish();
    // Should clear progress line
}
```

